A few months back, I did an Instagram live

01:01:17.040 --> 01:01:20.970
with Dr. Sean Mackey
who's an MD medical doctor

01:01:20.970 --> 01:01:23.710
and a PhD at Stanford School of Medicine

01:01:23.710 --> 01:01:26.220
that was recorded and
placed on my Instagram.

01:01:26.220 --> 01:01:27.460
If you want to check it out,

01:01:27.460 --> 01:01:30.180
we can provide a link to
that in the show notes.

01:01:30.180 --> 01:01:34.100
Dr. Mackey is the Chief
of the Division of Pain

01:01:34.100 --> 01:01:35.930
at Stanford School of Medicine.

01:01:35.930 --> 01:01:37.070
So he's a scientist.

01:01:37.070 --> 01:01:40.070
He studies pain and he
treats patients dealing

01:01:40.070 --> 01:01:42.100
with various forms of
pain, whole body pain,

01:01:42.100 --> 01:01:45.230
like fibromyalgia, acute pain, et cetera.

01:01:45.230 --> 01:01:47.170
And he shared with me
something very interesting,

01:01:47.170 --> 01:01:52.162
which is that anytime you
hear or see the word syndrome,

01:01:52.162 --> 01:01:55.740
that means the medical
